objectives.name: Primary Efficacy Objective
objectives.text: To demonstrate the superiority of palbociclib in combination with fulvestrant (with or without goserelin) over fulvestrant alone (with or without goserelin) in prolonging investigator-assessed PFS in women with HR+/HER2-negative metastatic breast cancer whose disease has progressed on prior endocrine therapy.

objectives.name: Tumor Control Objective
objectives.text: To compare measures of tumor control between the treatment arms.

objectives.name: Safety and Tolerability Objective
objectives.text: To compare safety and tolerability between the treatment arms.

objectives.name: Palbociclib Pharmacokinetic Objective
objectives.text: To evaluate trough concentrations of palbociclib when given in combination with fulvestrant or fulvestrant plus goserelin, compared to historical palbociclib data.

objectives.name: Fulvestrant and Goserelin Pharmacokinetic Objective
objectives.text: To compare fulvestrant and goserelin trough concentrations when given in combination with palbociclib to those when given without palbociclib.

objectives.name: Exposure-Response Objective
objectives.text: To explore correlations between palbociclib exposures and efficacy/safety findings in this patient population.

objectives.name: Patient Reported Outcomes Objective
objectives.text: To compare Patient Reported Outcomes measures between treatment arms.

objectives.name: Biomarker Objective
objectives.text: To characterize alterations in genes, proteins, and ribonucleic acids (RNAs) relevant to the cell cycle, drug targets, tumor sensitivity and/or resistance.

objectives.name: Subgroup Analysis Objective
objectives.text: To conduct subgroup analysis for primary and secondary endpoints in stratified groups.

endpoints.name: Progression-Free Survival (PFS)
endpoints.text: Progression-Free Survival (PFS) as assessed by the Investigator.

endpoints.name: Overall Survival (OS)
endpoints.text: Overall Survival (OS).

endpoints.name: Survival Probabilities
endpoints.text: 1-year, 2-year, and 3-year survival probabilities.

endpoints.name: Objective Response (OR)
endpoints.text: Objective Response (OR): Complete Response (CR) or Partial Response (PR).

endpoints.name: Duration of Response (DR)
endpoints.text: Duration of Response (DR).

endpoints.name: Clinical Benefit Response (CBR)
endpoints.text: Clinical Benefit Response (CBR): CR or PR or Stable Disease (SD) ≥24 weeks.

endpoints.name: Adverse Events and Laboratory Abnormalities
endpoints.text: Type, incidence, severity (as graded by the National Cancer Institute Common Terminology Criteria for Adverse Events [NCI CTCAE] v4.0), seriousness and relationship to study medications of Adverse Events (AEs) and any laboratory abnormalities.

endpoints.name: Trough Plasma Concentrations
endpoints.text: Trough plasma concentration of palbociclib, fulvestrant and goserelin (if applicable) in the subgroup of approximately 40 patients included in the initial safety review.

endpoints.name: Patient Reported Outcomes (PRO)
endpoints.text: PRO endpoints such as global quality of life symptoms and functioning assessed using the European Organisation for Research and Treatment of Cancer Quality of Life Instrument (EORTC QLQ-C30) and European Organisation for Research and Treatment of Cancer Breast Cancer Module (EORTC QLQ-BR23) and Dimension Health State EuroQoL Score (EQ-5D)and time to deterioration (TTD) in pain endpoint.

endpoints.name: Tumor Tissue Biomarkers
endpoints.text: Tumor tissue biomarkers, including genes (eg, copy numbers of CCND1 and CDKN2A, PIK3CA mutations), proteins (eg, Ki67, pRb, CCNE1), and RNA expression (eg, cdk4, cdk6).
